# API Blueprint Bartender

A sample api that uses a bartender to demo api blueprint

## Group Inventory

Inventory resources

### Beer Collection [/inventory/beers]

#### Get beers [GET]

Returns the complete inventory of beers.

+ Response 200 (application/json;charset=UTF-8)

    Inventory of beers.
    
    + Attributes
        :[](common/status.apib)
        + results (array, required)
            + (object)
                :[](resources/beer.apib)
                
#### Add a beer [POST]

Inserts a beer into the inventory.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes
        :[](resources/beer.apib)
        
+ Response 200 (application/json;charset=UTF-8)

    Beer added.
    
    + Attributes
        :[](common/status.apib)
        
+ Response 400 (application/json;charset=UTF-8)

    Invalid request such as invalid/missing beer properties.
    
    + Attributes
        :[](common/error_400.apib)
        
+ Response 401 (application/json;charset=UTF-8)

    Bartender credentials not provided.
    
    + Attributes
        :[](common/error_401.apib)
        
